# Container root's authorized_keys.
#
# Copy this file to authorized_keys (without the .example suffix) and paste
# one public key per line. You need the root public key from EACH Proxmox VE
# node so 'pvecm qdevice setup <host>' can SSH in and install the cluster
# certificate.
#
# On every PVE node, run:
#
#   cat /root/.ssh/id_rsa.pub      # or /root/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
#
# If no key exists, generate one with:
#
#   ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -N "" -f /root/.ssh/id_rsa
#
# Example (do not use these literally — they are placeholders):
#
#   ssh-rsa AAAAB3Nza...== root@pve01
#   ssh-rsa AAAAB3Nza...== root@pve02
#
# Ownership and permissions are auto-fixed by the entrypoint on container
# start, so it does not matter what UID created this file on the host.
